
# recipe for creating a spack env and building trilinos/stk

Note that this recipe assumes you are a Sierra developer,
working with STK inside a clone of Sierra code.

The scripts used below will assume that you have these directories:
/fgs/$USER/stk-cmake-testing
/fgs/$USER/code (<-- sierra code)
These directories can be changed by setting variables that the
scripts below use. See inside the scripts if you are brave.

$ cd /fgs/$USER/code

# do this next step once. create/setup spack and TPLs
$ source stk/stk_integration_tests/cmake_install_test/stk_spack_create_env.sh

# do this each time you want to build stk using tribits/cmake
$ ./stk/stk_integration_tests/cmake_install_test/build_stk_using_cmake

# other build configurations include:
build_stk_serial_using_cmake
build_stk_no_tests_using_cmake
build_stk_no_stk_search_util_using_cmake
build_stk_no_stk_mesh_using_cmake
build_stk_no_stk_io_using_cmake

